It offers health plans for families, children, and the aged, blind, and disabled, as well as prescription drug plans. The company operates its business through three segments: Medicaid Health Plans, Medicare Health Plans and Medicare PDPs. segment includes plans for beneficiaries of TANF, SSI, ABD, MLTC programs and other state-based programs that are not part of the Medicaid program, such as CHIP. Medicaid Health Plans segment generates revenues primarily from premiums received from the states in which it operates health plans. The Medicare prescription drug plan segment offers stand-alone Medicare Part D coverage to Medicare-eligible beneficiaries.
